Data engineers spends
significant effort and time

performing tasks like

Similar to building data

Every time a request

data engineer will

This approach is slow,
expensive, and ineffective.
AWS Glue blueprint addresses this problem
by offering framework for you to build
and share reusable Glue workflows.
Now let's take a closer look

at the process of
building Glue blueprints.
AWS Glue blueprint provides organization
a mechanism to develop, share
and reuse complex ETL workflow.
They assist ETL developer to generate

and publish templates of
commonly asked ETL workflow

that analysts or other
non-developer can consume

and execute jobs without
having to write code.

You can see Glue blueprint
lifecycle in this slide
with series of steps.

Step one, data engineer
identifies data injection pattern
and creates blueprints.
A blueprint in AWS Glue is a zip archive

that consists of a blueprint
configuration file,
a layout generator script,

and optional ETL scripts
and supporting file.

Step two, data engineers
shares this blueprint
via source control tool or S3.

Step three, non-developers
persona can easily register

and use this blueprint
using a user interface
where they provide input as parameters.
Finally, blueprint uses these parameters
to generate AWS Glue workflow

and users can simply
execute these workflow
to ingest and transform data.
Now that you know what is Glue blueprint,

let's look at the scenario
and data set for this demo.

in building data lake

is to convert row file
to columnar file format

that Parquet file format

One of the main challenges

The configuration file
